  "texts": [
    "At the model training stage, the study used adversarial learning strategy.",
    "Additional fairness strategies tried include the inference strategy and \"alone strategy\".",
    "The inference strategy involved adding sensitive feature (race) to the input for training and removing it for prediction while the alone strategy involved training the model separately on each race group.",
    "According to S5, using weight loss function to balance race reduced the TPR, TNR, and accuracy for all race groups except Pacific Islanders.",
    "For all the three metrics used, no single strategy was always the best, however, the inference strategy recorded the most frequent best performance but it is also the worst in terms of fairness."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}